                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/304.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-02T23:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1912—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Duty on the shipment of arms and ammunition on steamer <hi rend="italic"
                        >Monterey</hi> is estimated by Minister of Hacienda at about $16,000 gold,
                    based on weight according to invoice. American colony will find it extremely <pb
                        facs="0889" n="773" xml:id="pg_773"/> difficult to make this payment.
                    Perhaps Government here could take part of arms and ammunition in payment of
                    duties. Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
